{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783054324,"nonce":"KR6tUlMt3KPiCmBgXEM70RejlAs=","message":"PR 4a merged (#72, squash 3e7e28d): SQLite introspection + schema stores + the core canonicalization seams a schema-less, unnamed-constraint backend needs.\n\n- introspect.rs: SchemaIntrospect via sqlite_master + the table-valued PRAGMA functions (pragma_table_info / foreign_key_list / index_list / index_xinfo). Reads tables into one unqualified schema; declared types map to their SQLite affinity's representative; AUTOINCREMENT detected via a quote/comment-aware keyword scan of the CREATE TABLE text; PK from table_info ordinals (only the single-column INTEGER rowid alias forced NOT NULL); uniques/indexes split by index_list origin; FK omitted-parent-column lists resolved to the parent PK; partial-index predicate and FixedBytes width recovered from the stored DDL; trailing implicit-ASC index directions trimmed; internal (sqlite_*) and bookkeeping (__squealy_*) objects excluded (and the renderer reserves those prefixes).\n\n- Schema stores: SchemaRefactorStore / SchemaMetadataStore / SchemaPublishHistoryStore in __squealy_-prefixed tables (SQLite has no schema to hold them), created lazily, existence checked via sqlite_master.\n\n- Core seams (all default-preserving, so PG/MySQL unchanged): SchemaIntrospect gains canonical_schema_name (flatten, + fk references_schema), canonical_unique_name / canonical_foreign_key_name (column-derived names for constraints SQLite renders unnamed), canonical_default (bool/unsigned -\u003e integer, numeric/oversized-unsigned -\u003e raw text), and has_namespaces (drop empty flattened schemas). canonicalize_model also coalesces same-named schemas and normalizes explicit NO ACTION FK actions and all-ascending/trailing-ASC index directions.\n\n- Tests run in default CI against in-memory SQLite: churn-free replan over a real derive model, faithful introspected-shape assertion, the three stores, and a suite of convergence edge cases (defaults, FixedBytes width, partial index, NO ACTION, index directions, non-rowid PK nullability, empty schema).\n\nCodex: 10 rounds, 18 findings (all real churn-convergence / robustness issues), clean pass. Verify green throughout (fmt / clippy -D warnings / test --all-features / compile_fail).\n\nRejected-for-now (documented; land with render_plan/parsing): table CHECK constraints and column collations (SQLite exposes them only in the CREATE TABLE text). Remaining for this bug: PR 4b (render_plan — the 12-step table rebuild) and views (39f4468).","files":null}]}